\title{Towards Reliable Stress Prediction: Creating a Benchmark Dataset from Social Media Content}

\author{anonymous}\ \ \ Anna Martin-Boyle\ \ \ Dongyeop Kang\\
        \texttt{\{jayar040,mart5877,dongyeop\}@umn.edu}}
        %jayar040@umn.edu \\ mart5877@umn.edu \\ dongyeop@umn.edu}
%Check the name with Anna

\begin{document}
\maketitle
\begin{abstract}
Mental Health is something that is a concern for many individuals. Even though it is just like any other health issue, improper and insufficient guidance to handle the effects of the condition is making these a significant problem in today's world. Sometimes, the problem is not even the insufficient guidance; it can be too much information which might make one assume to have an opposite condition and make way for multiple other new issues. Thus, to overcome such confusions, this paper talks about developing an informed data set having various conversations along with the type of stress it belongs to with the help of taxonomy, which can further be used to make a informed assessment of the condition based on the way the person is communicating.
\end{abstract}

