\begin{abstract}
This paper presents a groundbreaking method for enhancing mental health assessments, utilizing a meticulously categorized dataset of conversations labeled with specific stress categories through a validated taxonomy. Addressing the limitations of existing conversational agents, we highlight the poor and ambiguous performance of ChatGPT, emphasizing the need for improved natural language processing tools in mental health applications. Our proposed taxonomy, crucial for accurate categorization, undergoes rigorous verification by domain experts, ensuring methodological reliability. Beyond this foundational aspect, our study positions itself as a future tool for medical professionals, summarizing patients' current states through a few targeted questions, offering valuable insights for a more comprehensive clinical study. This research marks a significant stride towards informed mental health assessments, providing a promising avenue for more personalized interventions.

\end{abstract}

