\begin{abstract}
This paper presents a data resource that has been tailored towards the application of enhancing mental health assessments. This resource dataset of conversations ateed it stress tes ing a taxonomy validated by a mental health professional. Addressing the limitations of existing conversational agents, we highlight the poor and ambiguous performance of LLMs, emphasizing the need for improved natural language processing tools in mental health applications. To ensure methodological reliability, we incorporated feedback from a domain expert on the development of our taxonomy. Additionally, our resource can be used to develop future tools for medical professionals that can summarize patients' current states through a few targeted questions, offering valuable insights prior to the patient's examination. This research marks a significant stride towards informed mental health assessments, providing a promising avenue for more personalized interventions.

