To enhance the robustness and reliability of our dataset, we conducted a first pass of the annotation process on around 59 selected samples. This annotation process was vital in ensuring the accuracy and consistency of the data labels chosen from the taxonomy, particularly in light of the multi-dimensional taxonomy we employed. The involvement of two annotators played a significant role in mitigating potential bias and subjectivity.
\bigbreak
To assess the quality and agreement among the annotators and to measure the subjectivity between them, we monitored inter-annotator metrics like Cohen's Kappa and Krippendorff's Alpha scores. Additionally, we observed ambiguity in the results when the tests were conducted using both ChatGPT 3.5 and ChatGPT 4. Figure [3] and figure[4], depicting these metrics respectively, provide valuable insights into the level of agreement and disagreement among the annotators, shedding light on the intricacies of label assignment for future passes of annotation and taxonomy refinement.

