To see the distinctive features of each dataset, see Table \ref{tab:dataset_comparison}. Our primary focus revolves around the rich textual content extracted from these datasets, strategically complemented by pertinent tags and labels. This curated summary aims not only to illuminate the core elements of the datasets but also to provide a holistic perspective for a more nuanced exploration of the data landscape. To achieve a comprehensive and well-distributed representation of various data categories, we supplemented the aggregated dataset with syntactic data. This additional dataset, comprising approximately 49.03\% of the complete data, contributes significantly to a more nuanced understanding of different stress categories. The remaining 50.97\% of the aggregated data is strategically divided, encompassing 31.65\% Dreaddit data, 25.32\% Pair data, and 43.04\% Counsel data. This allocation ensures a balanced integration of diverse sources, enriching the dataset with a variety of perspectives.
\bigbreak
The sentences in the datasets not only capture an individual's experience of stress at a specific point in time but also encompass reflections on past stressors or concerns about potential future stress. Table \ref{tab:timeframe_data_example} illustrates instances of texts from the aggregated dataset indicating the stress encountered in the past, present, and anticipated in the future. Overall, the dataset comprises diverse textual entries, each accompanied by essential metadata, including the text content, assigned category and subcategory labels, text length, and the percentage of both positive and negative sentiment, allowing for a nuanced exploration of stress-related expressions.

