\title{Towards Reliable Stress Prediction: Creating a Benchmark Dataset from Social Media Content}

\author{anonymous}\ \ \ Anna Martin-Boyle\ \ \ Dongyeop Kang\\
        \texttt{\{jayar040,mart5877,dongyeop\}@umn.edu}}
        %jayar040@umn.edu \\ mart5877@umn.edu \\ dongyeop@umn.edu}
%Check the name with Anna

\begin{document}
\maketitle
\begin{abstract}
This paper introduces a groundbreaking method for enhancing mental health assessments by leveraging a meticulously categorized dataset of diverse conversations, each labeled with specific stress categories curated with a validated taxonomy. Additionally, we address the limitations of existing conversational agents, highlighting the poor and ambiguous performance of ChatGPT and emphasizing the need for improvement in natural language processing tools for mental health applications. The proposed taxonomy, crucial for accurate categorization, undergoes rigorous verification by domain experts, ensuring the reliability of our methodology.Beyond this foundational aspect, our study positions itself  as a valuable tool for medical professionals on summarizing the current state of patients by answering a few questions, thereby providing valuable insights that contribute to a more comprehensive clinical study. This research marks a significant stride towards informed mental health assessments, offering a promising avenue for more personalized and effective interventions.
\end{abstract}

