before_text:
\section{Dataset}

\subsection{Types of available Data Sources}
The problem statement can include various data sources, each offering distinct advantages and challenges. The first type involves individuals providing labels for their text data, offering a direct perspective but introducing potential bias. The second type employs third-party annotators to reduce bias but may result in varying labels due to annotator subjectivity. The third type leverages medical professionals to assign labels, ensuring the authenticity of tags but presenting challenges in data collection. Lastly, the fourth type utilizes ChatGPT to label text data, benefiting from pre-existing knowledge but acknowledging the limitations of achieving perfect predictive accuracy, even with advanced technology.It can also be challenging as it will not be verified by any human and will be a direct annotation from machine. The choice of data source entirely depends on the objectives and the research considerations.
\subsection{Selected Data Source and Rationale}

After carefully considering various data source options, we ultimately opted for a data utilization strategy involving the second type, where the data consists of texts provided by the speaker and is subsequently annotated by third-party individuals. This approach is a pragmatic choice, given that we are annotating data from three distinct datasets we have meticulously collected. Using third-party annotators helps mitigate individual bias and subjectivity in the labeling process. Furthermore, this method allows for a more rigorous and collaborative review of the data, ensuring that the labels generated are accurate and reflect the underlying context.\\

The data obtained through this strategy will play a pivotal role in our research, as it forms the foundation for our comprehensive taxonomy, which will be elaborated upon in subsequent sections.\\

\subsection{Curated Data Compilation}

The work relies mainly on three distinct datasets, each providing valuable insights into the research statement. \\

\begin{itemize}
    \item The first dataset [dreaddit], sourced from \citet{turcan-mckeown-2019-dreaddit}, is a comprehensive collection comprising 2837 training and 715 testing records. It encompasses a diverse array of input features, including social media texts, associated labels representing mental health issues, confidence scores, and various other related metrics. The anticipated outcomes span a range of mental health conditions, such as relationships, anxiety, PTSD, assistance, homelessness, almost homelessness, domestic violence, survivors of abuse, stress, and food pantry. Figure [2] shows the counts of the labels in the test dataset.
\end{itemize}
\begin{itemize}
\item The second dataset [pair] \citet{min2022pair} focuses on the brief interactions between the counselors and the clients, offering insights into various levels of reflective listening skills. It consists of 318 records and includes client statements, typically presented to counseling trainees paired with counseling responses that exemplify different levels of reflective quality, spanning low quality, medium quality, and high quality.

