after_text:
\item The pair dataset \citet{min2022pair} focuses on the brief interactions between the counselors and the clients, offering insights into various levels of reflective listening skills. It consists of 318 records and includes client statements, typically presented to counseling trainees paired with counseling responses that exemplify different levels of reflective quality, spanning low quality, medium quality, and high quality.
\end{itemize}
\begin{itemize}
\item 
Counsel data \citet{bertagnolli2020counsel} revolves around councelchat.com, an exemplary expert community platform aimed at assisting counselors in building their professional reputation and fostering meaningful connections with potential clients. This dataset comprises 568 records and revolves around therapists' responses to client inquiries, with users having the option to 'like' responses they find most valuable.
\end{itemize}
\bigbreak
Table 2 visually engaging table serves as a snapshot, encapsulating the distinctive features within each dataset. Our primary focus revolves around the rich textual content extracted from these datasets, strategically complemented by pertinent tags and labels. This curated summary aims not only to illuminate the core elements of the datasets but also to provide a holistic perspective for a more nuanced exploration of the data landscape.To achieve a comprehensive and well-distributed representation of various data categories, we supplemented the aggregated dataset with syntactic data. This additional dataset, comprising approximately 49.03\% of the complete data, contributes significantly to a more nuanced understanding of different stress categories. The remaining 50.97\% of the aggregated data is strategically divided, encompassing 31.65\% Dreaddit data, 25.32\% Pair data, and 43.04\% Counsel data. This allocation ensures a balanced integration of diverse sources, enriching the dataset with a variety of perspectives.

The sentences in the datasets not only capture an individual's experience of stress at a specific point in time but also encompass reflections on past stressors or concerns about potential future stress. The table [3] illustrates instances of texts from the aggregated dataset indicating the stress encountered in the past, present, and anticipated in the future. Overall, the dataset comprises diverse textual entries, each accompanied by essential metadata, including the text content, assigned category and subcategory labels, text length, and the percentage of both positive and negative sentiment, allowing for a nuanced exploration of stress-related expressions.

