before_text:
To enhance the robustness and reliability of our dataset, we conducted multiple passes of the annotation process performed by human annotators on randomly selected samples, focusing on refining the taxonomy and its associated guidelines. This iterative annotation approach played a pivotal role in ensuring the accuracy and consistency of the data labels derived from the taxonomy, particularly given the multi-dimensional nature of the employed taxonomy.The deliberate involvement of multiple annotators aimed to mitigate potential bias and subjectivity, contributing to the overall reliability of the dataset. Evaluation metrics, such as Cohen's Kappa \citet{cohen1960coefficient} and Krippendorff's Alpha scores \citet{krippendorff1970estimating}, were employed to assess the annotation quality in each pass. Notably, the scores exhibited improvement, progressing from 0.44 in the first pass to 0.63 in the latest pass.The figure 1 provides a comprehensive overview of the evolving performance of our annotation process over multiple passes.This positive trend in scores signifies the refinement and maturity of the current taxonomy and annotation process, highlighting the evolving accuracy and reliability of our labeled dataset.Each pass underwent updates based on valuable input from medical professional and evaluations of interannotator scores.

\\

