With this in mind, we start by generating all possible motifs with 3 vertices, a minimal form other than a single edge---this gives us 69 non-isomorphic motifs. To create larger motifs, we pick two size-3 motifs from all possible pairs, join them at all possible nodes, and only keep the non-isomorphic ones, resulting in size-6 motifs. We conduct this process one more round with pairs of size-3 and 6 motifs to produce size-9 motifs.\footnote{As we are joining motifs at their nodes, the total number of nodes for size-6 and 9 motifs can be smaller than 6 and 9, respectively.}
